```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "partition": "rise",
    "working_directory": "/home/eecs/arinchang/overparam_spur_corr",
    "node": "ace",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks": 1,
    "cores_per_task": 6,
    "gpus": 1,
    "time_limit": "4-00:00",
    "stdout": "slurm_logs/slurm.%N.%j..out",
    "stderr": "slurm_logs/slurm.%N.%j..err",
    "python_environment": "sagawa_dp",
    "python_script": "run_expt_dp.py",
    "script_arguments": "-id dp_width32_erm -s confounder -d CelebA --noise 1.0 --max_per_sample_grad_norm 1.0 -t Blond_Hair -c Male --lr 0.01 --batch_size 128 --weight_decay 0.0001 --model resnet10vw --n_epochs 50 --train_from_scratch --resnet_width 32"
  }
}
```

This script utilizes Slurm for job scheduling and resource allocation. It runs a Python script named "run_expt_dp.py" using a specific environment "sagawa_dp". The script utilizes a "resnet10vw" model, the CelebA dataset, and implements DP-SGD with specific parameters for noise, gradient norm, and weight decay. The script runs for 50 epochs with a batch size of 128.
